review_blob: This Pilsener is refreshing, dry and crisp. It pours a nice yellow tone with high carbonation. Head is high with good retention. I enjoyed this in a hot day, so I find it very proper for thirst quencher. Nice beer, not the greatest but I can drink two or three easily.

Pours a nice yellow deep tone with low carbonation. Head is low with zero retention. Smell is zesty, low malt smell. Taste is clean refreshing with some bitternes at the end. It is the perfect beer to enjoy in a sunny day. It is quiete similar to some american lagers, but with more body. Dont like too much the sweetness aftertaste

This is a beer with great appearence, pours a nice brown dark honey color. head is big creamy beige in color with low retention. lacing is medium. carbonation high. It has some sediment at the bottom og the glass. It is a nice thirst quencher with dry taste.

Pours a hazzy golden tone similar to pineapple juice. head is medium with medium retention. High carbonation. Smell is coriander, citrus and malt. Some sweetnes. It is a really enjoyable beer. I would not hesitate to have it regularly. Taste is refreshing and crisp.

Pours a dark caramel color, head is high with poor retention. Lacing is medium. Smell caramel like and little or no presence of hoppines. taste is boring with some refreshing character. It is not the beer I would like to have normally.

Wow, this is the firts beer I can not finish. very high alcohol content and marked ethanol flavor. Dark golden color, head with no retention. I was planning to drink a can of 500ml but my intuition said NO!.

Awful!

Pours a nice pale yellow color. head is medium with low retention and low lacing. Smell is rich, complex, high presence of sweet barley malt. I am pleasantly surprised and I enjoyed it. It is a very good lager beer. I can buy it again without hesitate

Nice golden color pured on my glass. Medium white head that dissipates quickly. It has a barly malt smell with little hop presence. Taste is nice with good balance. I enjoyed this beer as any good lager. It has good aftertaste and it is refreshing. Really good.
It pours a dark chocolate tone. head is thin a beige. It has a roasted coffee smell with a hint of hops. Not my favorite beer flavor. Too pricey for what I get. Definitely not my preference.

I had this while I have a cold and not sure if it is the fair taste test. It pors a hazy golden tone on my glass. I can feel the hoppiness clearly before I try it. Taste is too bitter to me. It is a nice beer but price here is too high. I think I am not going to buy it again.
Pours a hazy yellow tone low carbonation. Smell is weak. Taste is a little hoppy with a touch of sweet barley malt. Not my preferred beer but would drink it anytime in a hot humid weather.

Pours a dark chocolate color, with thin head with no retention at all. Smell is caramel, little very little hops and a hint of roasted barley malt. Taste is less than I was expecting. It is a little watery. Hops with almost no presence. Nice as a thirst quencher. Too much money for what I got

A nice yellow appearence, low retention head. Some apple smell with a hint of malt. really watery mouthfeel , crisp clean and refreshing  ideal for a hot weather and low calorie intake diet. Not bad for a low alcoholic beer. Much much better thatn Becks NA.

Served in a pint glass, pours a nice translucid yellow color. medium head with good retention thru the taste test. Oregano an coriander like smell. A little odd taste to my preferences. I enjoy this beer from time to time, not on a daily basis. I am not really sure if i will try it once again, but it was a nice experience to drink one.
weak head, nice amber color, sweet malt aroma. It has a pleasant refreshing feel. Better than any light american beer
Nice appearence, sweet aroma and nice golden coloor. A Little bitter to my taste, nice to have one before lunch
